&lt;p&gt;   Protocol compatibility can be facilitated if a Struct, that has been defined as an extension of a previous Struct by adding fields at the end of the older version, can read a message of an older version by ignoring the absence of the missing new fields. Reading the missing fields should be allowed by the definition of these fields (they have to be nullable).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Tested by adding unit tests around Schema.read in both directions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


